options.title: --version
options.description: Use the specified version when finding resources for formula. If no version is specified, the current version for formula will be used.

options.title: --package-name
options.description: Use the specified package-name when finding resources for formula. If no package name is specified, it will be inferred from the formula's stable URL.

options.title: --extra-packages
options.description: Include these additional packages when finding resources.

options.title: --exclude-packages
options.description: Exclude these packages when finding resources.

options.title: --to-tag

options.title: --keep-tmp
options.description: Retain the temporary directory containing the new repository clone.

options.title: --commit
options.description: Use the specified commit as the start commit.

options.title: --before
options.description: Use the commit at the specified date as the start commit.

options.title: --update
options.description: Update all vendored Gems to the latest version.

options.title: --edit
options.description: Edit aliases in a text editor. Either one or all aliases may be opened at once. If the given alias doesn't exist it'll be pre-populated with a template.

options.title: --upgrade
options.description: Automatically upgrade your installed formulae. If the Caskroom exists locally Casks will be upgraded as well. Must be passed with start.

options.title: --cleanup
options.description: Automatically clean brew's cache and logs. Must be passed with start.

options.title: --enable-notification
options.description: Send a notification when the autoupdate process has finished successfully, if terminal-notifier is installed & found. Note that currently a new experimental notifier runs automatically on macOS Catalina and newer, without requiring any external dependencies. Must be passed with start.

options.title: --immediate
options.description: Starts the autoupdate command immediately, instead of waiting for one interval (24 hours by default) to pass first. Must be passed with start.

options.title: --file
options.description: Read the Brewfile from this location. Use --file=- to pipe to stdin/stdout.

options.title: --global
